# devinity-web

Next.js frontend for Devinity. Scope: `DVN`. Port **3001** in dev.

## Structure

```
src/
  app/               # App Router pages, layouts, route handlers
    components/      # Page-scoped components (Sidebar, AppShell, …)
    api/             # Route handlers
    sign-in/
  components/        # Shared app components (AuthGuard, …)
  hooks/             # React Query hooks (e.g. hooks/users/)
  providers/
  lib/               # Auth client, thin third-party wrappers
```

## Patterns

- App Router, Turbopack (`next dev --port 3001`, `next build --turbopack`)
- `"use client"` for interactive pages/components
- Styled-components: colocate `*.styles.tsx` with components
- Shared UI from `@repo/ui`; data types from `@repo/api`
- Auth: Better-Auth client in `@lib/auth-client`
- Data fetching: `@tanstack/react-query` hooks in `src/hooks/`

## Path aliases

Follow `tsconfig.json` paths: `@/`, `@lib/`, `@components/`.

## API routes

- `src/app/api/**/route.ts` — thin handlers, delegate to services if needed

## Testing

- Unit: Vitest + `@repo/vitest-config/next`, `vitest.setup.ts`
- E2e: Playwright in `test/e2e/*.e2e-spec.ts` — `pnpm test:e2e`

## Lint

- `eslint . --max-warnings 0`
